	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Sun, Jul 25th 1:01 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=383682"><span id=" ">Riveo</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">3 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>It can be done utilizing sneak and a non-kos friend.&nbsp;&nbsp;Invis past the front gargs, turn to the right and kind of hide in the corner behind the pillars.  You will be out of the skeletons agro range from there.  Target a skeleton and use sneak until you are actually sneaking and they con indifferent.  Now have your friend hail Capt. Rottgrime to turn him around.  He will then be indifferent to you also.  Edge up behind the line of skeletons until you are close enough to trade with the capt. but so that you are still behind the line of soldiers.  Doing this you should be able to turn in the braids and work up your faction.<br/><br/>You may want to wait until the goons leave on patrol as they have a pretty large agro range.  I got my tunare woodelf bard up to dubious in DE illusion this way but I was too tired of berzerkers to go any further.  Good Luck!<br/><br/>Riveo Lindor - 65 Maestro<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun Jul 25 01:02:06 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
