	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=92268"><span id=" ">gadiaton</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">51 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Good [4.25]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Here is my experience getting this mallet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Started out with Threatening faction.  Tried the Dark Elf potion - didn't change faction at all...if it used to work it does not anymore.  So I pulled Rottgrime way out of the Outpost (easy to split him from his troops as a 58 monk, do it between 10pm and 6am to avoid the guards) and had my 64 Chanter bud try to charm him.  Did not work...he got resisted every time.  So Chanter zoned at book and I pulled Rottgrime way out from Outpost again, FD'd and hit sneak.  When he started walking away I got up and managed to turn in 8 Braids while following him (kind of hard to do since Rottgrime runs off and attacks any nearby mobs). Luckily 8 braids got me to Dubious so I at least did not have to worry about pulling him out of Outpost again. I had to turn in 200 more braids just to get to apprehensive. 80 more braids got me to indiff, and only 40 more got me to amiable so that I could get my Sledgemallet.  The best place to get Braids is at the ruins in OT at -1500, +500. I was able to get about 30-40 braids (and 200-250pp in cash and gems) an hour there.  Braids drop off the Bezerkers in case you don't know. Hope this helps.<br/><br/>Title should say Worker Sledgemallet and Faction...duh...oh well.<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Sep 18 20:27:36 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
